        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 19 1873</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am greatly obliged by the gift of the first number of your magnificent work on the fossils of M<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Léberon.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I really do not feel worthy of your repeated acts of generosity.</p>
<p>With the most sincere respect I remain dear Sir | yours very faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Gaudry had written the section on vertebrates in <hi rend="italic">Animaux fossiles du Mont Léberon (Vaucluse)</hi> (Gaudry <hi rend="italic">et al.</hi> 1873). CD’s copy is in the Darwin Library–Down.</note>
        </div>        
            
